--[[ Lua code. See documentation: https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/ --]]

--[[ The onLoad event is called after the game save finishes loading. --]]
function onLoad()
    importer = getObjectFromGUID("f46dd6")
    addHotkey("Make Check", makeCheck, false)
end
---DiscardTopCard
function makeCheck(color, hovered, pointer, up)
  if color == "Red" or color == "White" then
    discardTopRed()
  elseif color == "Blue" or color == "Green" then
    discardTopBlue()
  end
end

function discardTopBlue()
  deckBlue = getObjectFromGUID("bb2870").getObjects()
  if deckBlue[1].tag == "Deck" then
    deckBlue[1].takeObject({
      position          = {-14.14, 1.83, 6.70},
      flip              = true,
    })
  else
    deckBlue[1].flip()
    deckBlue[1].setPositionSmooth({-14.14, 1.83, 6.70})
    Wait.time(|| NewDeckBlue(), 1.5)
  end
end
function NewDeckBlue()
  discardBlue = getObjectFromGUID("a43ab5").getObjects()
  discardBlue[1].flip()
  discardBlue[1].setPositionSmooth({-10.62, 1.03, 6.69})
  discardBlue[1].shuffle()
  Wait.time(|| discardBlue[1].takeObject({
    position          = {-18.04, 3.51, 6.68},
    flip              = true,
  }), 0.3, 10)
end

function discardTopRed()
  deckRed = getObjectFromGUID("ff12ce").getObjects()
  if deckRed[1].tag == "Deck" then
    deckRed[1].takeObject({
      position          = {13.59, 1.83, -7.88},
      flip              = true,
    })
  else
    deckRed[1].flip()
    deckRed[1].setPositionSmooth({13.59, 1.83, -7.88})
    Wait.time(|| NewDeckRed(), 1.5)
  end
end
function NewDeckRed()
  discardRed = getObjectFromGUID("b98f37").getObjects()
  discardRed[1].flip()
  discardRed[1].setPositionSmooth({10.07, 1.23, -7.86})
  discardRed[1].shuffle()
  Wait.time(|| discardRed[1].takeObject({
    position          = {17.53, 3.51, -7.85},
    flip              = true,
  }), 0.3, 10)
end
function onObjectSpawn(object)
    if object.type == "Card" then
        importer.call("addUVSTransform", {obj = object, name = object.getName()})
    end
end

local promote = 'off'

function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "Auto Promote Off",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 90, 0},
        width          = 3000,
        height         = 600,
        font_size      = 340,
        color          = {0.5, 0.5, 0.5},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
        tooltip        = "This text appears on mouseover.",
    }
    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    if promote == 'off' then
        promote = 'on' 
        obj.editButton({label = "Auto Promote On"})
        
        local players = Player.getPlayers()
        for _, player in ipairs(players) do
            tryPromotePlayer(player)
        end
    else
        promote = 'off'
        obj.editButton({label = "Auto Promote Off"})
    end
end

--::[[ Auto Player Promoter ]]::--
-- Version 1.0
-- By Kevin O'Mara (Quickle)
-- https://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561197997376704

--[[
This script runs in the background and makes sure all players are promoted so
they have "host" powers (delete/spawn/copy/paste/etc.) For more info on host:
http://berserk-games.com/knowledgebase/player-roles/

Additionally, if a player gets "demoted", the script takes care they are never
automatically promoted again (i.e. when the player drops and re-joins the match,
the game is saved and loaded in the future, or time is rewound/fast forwarded).

Players are promoted at the following times:
* All players are promoted each time the game first loads (including Undo/Redo).
* New players are promoted upon joining the match.

Whether a player is "demoted" is recorded at the following times:
* All players are recorded when the game saves (including auto saves).
* Individual players are recorded when they leave the match.

Undo / Redo
* Undo - A demoted player may become promoted again if time rewinds to a point
  when they were previously promoted.
* Redo - A player will never become demoted when time fast forwards, even if
  they had previously been demoted at that autosave.
--]]



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--[[ CONFIGURATION  ]]----------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--[[
You can modify the script's behavior by changing these variables:
--]]

-- When true, this object is interactable by Players.
-- You may wish to lock this object and hide it somewhere. To do so, simply:
--  1. Set this value to 'true' & save the script.
--  2. Move the object somewhere & save the game.
--  3. Set this value back to 'false' & save the script.
local objectIsInteractable = true

-- When true, a chat message announces each time a player is automatically
-- promoted or would have been promoted (but wasn't because they are "demoted").
-- Lets players know they are being promoted by a script rather than the host.
local chatEnabled = false

-- When true, debug information is written the log window (host only).
local loggingEnabled = false


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--[[ SCRIPT CODE  ]]------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--[[ Utility Methods ]]---------------------------------------------------------

local function _log(element, label)
    -- Log a message with the prefix "AutoPlayerPromoter: ".
    -- Wrapper for `log()`: https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/base/#log
    if loggingEnabled then
        log(element, "AutoPlayerPromoter: " .. tostring(label))
    end
end

local function _printToAll(message)
    -- Print a message to chat, but only if `chatEnabled` is `true`.
    -- Wrapper for `print()`: https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/base/#print
    if chatEnabled then
        printToAll(message)
    end
end

local function _playerAsTable(player)
    -- Return a <Player> object (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/) as a
    -- simple key-value table, which can be expanded by the built-in logging
    -- method: https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/base/#log
    return {
        steam_name  = player.steam_name,
        steam_id    = player.steam_id,
        promoted    = player.promoted,
        host        = player.host,
        admin       = player.admin,
        color       = player.color,
        team        = player.team,
        seated      = player.seated,
        blindfolded = player.blindfolded,
        lift_height = player.lift_height,
    }
end
--//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////



--[[ Player Promotion Tracker ]]------------------------------------------------
--[[
Keeps track of which players are demoted and offers a method to promote players.
--]]

-- Steam IDs of Players who have had their promotion revoked.
-- @type: Set<string>
local _demotedPlayerSteamIds = {}

function isOnDemotedPlayerList(player)
    -- @param player <Player> (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/)
    return _demotedPlayerSteamIds[player.steam_id] ~= nil
end

function isPromoted(player)
    -- @param player <Player> (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/)
    return player.promoted or player.host
end

function tryPromotePlayer(player)
    -- @param player <Player> (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/)
    if promote == 'on' then
        if isOnDemotedPlayerList(player) then
            _log(_playerAsTable(player), "Will not promote player because they are on the Demoted Player List: ")
            _printToAll("AutoPlayerPromoter: Not promoting player " .. tostring(player.steam_name) .. ", because they were demoted by host.")
        elseif isPromoted(player) then
            _log(_playerAsTable(player), "Will not promote player because they are already promoted or host: ")
        else
            _log(_playerAsTable(player), "Promoting player: ")
            _printToAll("AutoPlayerPromoter: Promoting " .. tostring(player.steam_name))
            player.promote()
        end
    end
end

function savePlayerPromotionState(player)
    -- @param player <Player> (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/)
    if isPromoted(player) then
        _log(_playerAsTable(player), "Saving player's promotion status. Player is <promoted>: ")
        _demotedPlayerSteamIds[player.steam_id] = nil
    else
        _log(_playerAsTable(player), "Saving player's promotion status. Player is <demoted>: ")
        _demotedPlayerSteamIds[player.steam_id] = {}
    end
end
--//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////



--[[ Event Hooks ]]-------------------------------------------------------------
--[[
Makes sure players are getting promoted and recorded at the right times by
responding to events.
--]]


function onPlayerConnect(player)
    -- @param player <Player> (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/)
    tryPromotePlayer(player)
end

function onPlayerDisconnect(player)
    -- @param player <Player> (https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/player/)
    savePlayerPromotionState(player)
end

function onSave()
    local players = Player.getPlayers()
    for _, player in ipairs(players) do
        savePlayerPromotionState(player)
    end

    saveData = JSON.encode(_demotedPlayerSteamIds)
    _log(saveData, "Saving script state: ")
    return saveData
end
--//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

list=''



function importDeck()
  cards = {}
  side = list:find('%[b]Side%[/b]')
  if side == nil then side = 1 / 0 end
  j = list:find('%[/url]')
  if j == nil then j = 0 end
  while  true do
    i, j, number, card = list:find('(%d+) ([^\n]*)', j)
    if i == nil then break end
    table.insert(cards, { number = number, card = trim(card), side = i > side })
  end
  for k, v in pairs(cards) do
    if images[string.lower(v.card)] == nil then
      print('ERROR: can\'t find image for card: ', v.card)
      goto continue
    end
    for i = 1, v.number do
      if v.side then
        position = { -18, 0, 3 }
      elseif k == 1 and i == 1 then
        position = { -18, 0, -3 }
      else
        position = { -18, 0, 0 }
      end
      card = spawnObject({ 
        type = 'CardCustom',
        rotation = { 0, 90, 0 },
        position = position
      })
      if imagesBack[string.lower(v.card)] != nil then
      	card.addContextMenuItem("UVS - Transform Card", transformCard, false)
      end
      card.setName(v.card)
      if errata[string.lower(v.card)] != nil then
      	card.setDescription("Errata: " .. errata[string.lower(v.card)])
      end
      card.setCustomObject({
        face = images[string.lower(v.card)],
        back = 'https://steamusercontent-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/2083534112071700900/E741482B971F45167F4A08CAC6F26B9D01362F97/'
      })
    end
    ::continue::
  end
end

function addUVSTransform(args)
    if imagesBack[string.lower(args["name"])] then
        args["obj"].addContextMenuItem("UVS - Transform Card", transformCard, false)
    end
end

function transformCard(_, _, obj)
  card = obj.getCustomObject()
  cardObj = obj.getData()
  if images[string.lower(cardObj.Nickname)] == card.face then
    card.face = imagesBack[string.lower(cardObj.Nickname)]
  else
    card.face = images[string.lower(cardObj.Nickname)]
  end
  obj.setCustomObject(card)
end

function trim(s)
  return (s:gsub('^%s*(.-)%s*$', '%1'))
end

function input_func(obj, color, input, stillEditing)
    list = input
end

function onload()

    local textbox = {}
    textbox.input_function = "input_func"
    textbox.function_owner = self
    textbox.label = "UVS Ultra Forum Code"
    textbox.width = 1000
    textbox.height = 600
    textbox.position = {0, 0.2, -0.2}
    textbox.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
    textbox.font_size = 50



    textbox.lineType = MultiLineNewLine
    self.createInput(textbox)

    local button = {}
    button.width = 1200
    button.height = 300
    button.function_owner = self
    button.position = {0, 0.2, 0.7}
    button.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
    button.click_function = "importDeck"
    button.label = 'Import'
    button.font_size = 200
    button.scale = {0.5,0.5,0.9}
    self.createButton(button)

end

function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "onIncrementDecrementClick",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "",
        position       = {0, 0.1, 0.25},
        rotation       = {0, 180, 0},
        width          = 600,
        height         = 300,
        font_size      = 340,
        color          = Color.Orange,
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    if save_state == nil or save_state == "" then
        script_state = {
            value = 0,
            label = "",
            use_prefix = false,
            light_font = false,
        }
    else
        script_state = JSON.decode(save_state)
    end
    self.createButton(params)
end

function onIncrementDecrementClick(obj, color, alt)
    if script_state.value == 0 then
        script_state.value = 1
        obj.editButton({color = Color.Red})
    elseif script_state.value == 1 then
        script_state.value = 2
        obj.editButton({color = Color.Yellow})
    else 
        script_state.value = 0
        obj.editButton({color = Color.Orange})
    end
end

        script_state = {
            value = 0,

            light_font = false,
        }
    else
        script_state = JSON.decode(save_state)
    end
    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    if Grid.show_lines == true then
        Grid.show_lines = false
        Grid.snapping = 1
        obj.editButton({label = "Grid On"})
    else 
        Grid.show_lines = true
        Grid.snapping = 3
        obj.editButton({label = "Grid Off"})
    end
    Grid.sizeX = 2.5
    Grid.sizeY = 3.5
end

function onIncrementDecrementClick(obj, color, alt)
    if alt then
        script_state.value = script_state.value - 1
    else
        script_state.value = script_state.value + 1
    end
    obj.editButton({label = script_state.value})
end

function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "onIncrementDecrementClick",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = 0,
        position       = {0, 0.1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 600,
        height         = 600,
        font_size      = 340,
        color          = {0.5, 0.5, 0.5},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    if save_state == nil or save_state == "" then
        script_state = {
            value = 0,
            label = "",
            use_prefix = false,
            light_font = false,
        }
    else
        script_state = JSON.decode(save_state)
    end
    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    if Grid.show_lines == true then
        Grid.show_lines = false
        Grid.snapping = 1
        obj.editButton({label = "Grid On"})
    else 
        Grid.show_lines = true
        Grid.snapping = 3
        obj.editButton({label = "Grid Off"})
    end
    Grid.sizeX = 2.5
    Grid.sizeY = 3.5
end

function onIncrementDecrementClick(obj, color, alt)
    if alt then
        script_state.value = script_state.value - 1
    else
        script_state.value = script_state.value + 1
    end
    obj.editButton({label = script_state.value})
end
